The age limit on suspending courses for business for college students in Guangxi can achieve 5 years - Xinhuanet Message from Nanning of the Xinhua News Agency on May 19 (journalist: Zhang Ying): according to information from Department of Education of Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region, various universities and colleges in Guangxi will implement flexible length of schooling and broaden the age limit for temporary absence from school for students, and the age limit for temporary absence from school for students at school can be extended by 2 to 5 years based on the original length of schooling, and the time for temporary absence from school for entrepreneurship can be regarded as the time for practical education. In order to promote the entrepreneurship and innovation ability of college students, departments of education and human resource and social security work together to establish the entrepreneurship platforms, to establish more off-campus practice teaching bases, university science parks, pioneer parks for college students and business incubation bases, to provide external guarantee for entrepreneurship for college students. According to related requirements, up until 2020, the innovation and entrepreneurship practice base of undergraduate colleges shall be at least 3000 m2 and that of higher vocational schools shall be at least 2000 m2. Governments encourage college students to establish the credit points for innovation and entrepreneurship, to give priority in transfer of specialty of students with excellent performance in innovation and entrepreneurship. Teachers in universities and colleges are required to take a temporary post in enterprises of related industries for at least two months each two years, so as to improve the awareness and ability of innovation and entrepreneurship education of the teachers. It is required by the Department of Education of Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region that various universities and colleges shall profoundly implement the innovation and entrepreneurship training plan for college students, to make each college student participate in one innovation and entrepreneurship training plan at school. Universities and colleges are required to organize students to participate in various types of innovation and entrepreneurship competitions, and certain expenditure support shall be provided.
